  "response_text": "In a bright, formal banquet room, a young female-presenting server in a white dress shirt, black vest, black bow tie, and name tag stands among round tables set with white tablecloths, plates, cups, and folded napkins. She has short dark hair and holds a yellow-and-red Starburst candy pack in one hand while looking down at it, as if considering the candy. Behind her, a young male-presenting server in the same black-and-white waiter uniform works at another table, arranging place settings. The room is pale and elegant, with many empty chairs, draped curtains, and buffet equipment in the background.\n\nThe male server becomes the focus. He turns from his work and looks to the side, then toward the person he is addressing, wearing a faint, knowing expression. His black bow tie, black vest, and name tag are visible against the white shirt as he appears to explain something. The visual setting then shifts into an exaggerated imagined scene: a warm living room with striped green wallpaper, a framed flower picture on the wall, a sunny window, a green armchair, a blue sofa, a potted plant, and a vase of bright flowers. A tiny dark fighter jet streaks into this domestic space, first glimpsed as a blur passing near the bouquet and then as a small aircraft hovering or flying around the room near the plant and furniture.\n\nFrom inside the tiny jet, a transparent targeting display overlays the living room. Through the cockpit view, the suited male server appears seated in the green armchair, holding Starburst candy, while a light-colored shaggy dog sits on the floor nearby. The jet’s controls and glowing green circular graphics sit along the bottom of the view, making the living room look like a miniature combat zone. The pilot is then shown close up: an adult man in a red flight helmet marked with a yellow emblem, a gray oxygen mask covering his mouth and nose, and a green flight suit with straps and patches. His eyes are focused and serious as he faces forward in the cockpit.\n\nThe tiny fighter jet flies low through the living room, seen from behind with wings outstretched and small pods under them. Purple exhaust or vapor glows behind it as it heads toward the seated server. White streaks trail through the air. In an extreme close view, the server holds a small pink square Starburst candy between his fingers and opens his mouth to eat it. Thin white streams or trails appear to shoot into or across the candy as he brings it to his lips, visually matching the idea from the dialogue context that “juiciness” is being fired into the Starburst.\n\nBack in the cockpit, the pilot glances around with wide, excited eyes as the room blurs behind him. The action then cuts to the shaggy cream-colored dog on the floor. The dog looks upward with its mouth open, then is hit by the same white gust-like streams. Its long fur and ears flap outward dramatically, first blown back and then settling as the dog sits there looking startled but unharmed.\n\nThe commercial returns to the banquet room. The young male server, now in close-up, looks unsettled and thoughtful, his eyes lowered as if reacting to the bizarre explanation. The female server stands in the foreground, slightly out of focus, still composed in her bow tie and vest, while he remains behind her, looking off to the side with a wary, confused expression. The formal dining room remains calm and orderly, contrasting with the chaotic tiny-jet fantasy.",
